0,'revision','',0),(164,1,'2012-11-23 03:18:01','2012-11-23 03:18:01','At Bumble Bees Nannies all nanny applicants are required to submit their updated resume as well as an Application form. If nannies have Early Childhood qualifications and/or at least 3 years’ experience they will be asked to come into the agency to discuss their experiences, qualifications, philosophies on raising children, why they stopped working with their last employer.   During this process we also discuss their interests, hobbies, and their reason for becoming a nanny. I find this information important to make a great match with a family.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div4\"></div>\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies also checks: \r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n<li>References</li>\r\n<li>Valid First Aid and CPR certification</li>\r\n<li>Up-to-date Police check. A vulnerable Persons Police Check will be conducted once a nanny has been offered a job</li>\r\n<li>Driver’s License details and/or passport, birth certificate</li>\r\n<li>Working status if they are not a Canadian citizen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nWhile going through their resume/CV we look for any loopholes/ gaps that they have missed and find out why they have missed out certain areas.\r\n\r\nWith Bumble Bees doing this process, it will eliminate the amount of work you need to do and the amount nannies calling you and coming into your home doing interviews. It can be confusing interviewing multiple candidates so let Bumble Bees do all the work,  finding the right nanny for you. Bumble Bees aims for families to only interview 2-4 nannies which we think will suit all your needs and requirements.\r\n\r\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process we are confident that we can find the right nanny for your family.','Nanny Screening Process','','publish','open','open','','nanny-screening-process','','','2012-12-02 01:09:07','2012-12-02 01:09:07','',154,'http://loca